  "unmapped_findings": [
    "The volume fraction of small angle grain boundaries increased greatly during deformation, exceeding 51% at true strain 0.27 for H90 (from 26% at 0.03, 31% at 0.10, 45% at 0.20).",
    "Schmid factor distribution: at true strain 0.03, >70% of retained austenite had Schmid factors 0.45-0.48; average decreased with strain; at 0.20, >60% had Schmid factor <0.40; at 0.27, volume fraction of austenite with Schmid factor <0.34 decreased to 5%.",
    "Fracture mode of H90 quasi-cleavage with features: flat 'class cleavage' facets, micropores, tear edges, secondary cracks, dimples, short curved river pattern, herringbone crack.",
    "Ms and Md30 temperatures calculated using empirical equations (2) and (3); C content in austenite measured by XRD using Eq. (1): αγ = 3.578 + 0.0330XC + 0.0056XAl + 0.00095XMn.",
    "In conclusion, the best combination of mechanical properties was achieved for the steel solution treated at 900°C for 1 h, attributed to TRIP effect and high dislocation density, with UTS of 836.4 MPa, YS of 473.6 MPa, and TE of 32% (note: text mentions 846 MPa in abstract, but 836.4 MPa in conclusion; discrepancy kept as in paper)."
  ]
